eep weekend block active. Keep PM config unchanged. Do not create any Sunday exception for V5a-eligible rows. Keep `max_bias=70` unchanged; observed |bias| 82.2 reinforces hard-cap caution. Continue waiting for alpha-tagged realized weekday/active-hour outcomes before any 20 UTC or alpha overlay change.\n\n**Next:** Re-run the 20 UTC analyzer and check the next weekday active-hour session for the first alpha-tagged outcome. If outcomes appear without `alpha_*` fields, patch instrumentation immediately.\n\n## 2026-05-03 03:35 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] BTC stays contested; ETH short intensified\n\n**Task:** Re-scan HL top-trader copy intelligence after P4 cooled from expanding risk into `range_mean_revert_friendly`, and verify whether BTC can upgrade from cautious bullish / contested.\n\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P1**.\n- Fresh tracker output: **BTC 6L/2S**, **ETH 2L/6S**, **SOL 2L/6S**.\n- Current top-book notional:\n  - **BTC:** longs **$14.57M** vs shorts **$4.32M** \u2192 net **+$10.26M long**\n ",
